<P>
FASHION; 
</P>
<P>
WHERE DEER AND ANTELOPE PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROCHELLE REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EAT YOUR HEART out, Ralph Lauren. Take notice, Vogue. Dana Korbin, owner of the 
quirky cow-motif shops, Udderly Perfect, in Santa Monica and Manhattan Beach, 
is now selling her beautiful collection of vintage Western, hand-tooled leather 
handbags. 
</P>
<P>
In buttery cowhide and adorned with squiggles and swirls or the Western deer 
and antelope, the bags usually have a zippered pocket and sometimes a velvet 
lining. 
</P>
