<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK GOLDSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEX, LIES AND: Color us astonished. Frank Magid Associates, a respected 
Iowa-based research firm, recently conducted a sexual attitude survey to 
determine, among other things, what performers people enjoyed listening to 
"during a sexual experience." 
</P>
<P>
(The survey was commissioned by "Hard Copy," a tabloid-TV show with an 
unquenchable fascination for such matters.) The results come as something of a 
shock. We'd have expected Madonna or Smokey Robinson (or at least Frank 
Sinatra) to emerge as winners. But Magid, who claims to have surveyed 1,000 
adults from age 18 to 49, insists that the most popular artist for sexual 
encounters is . . . Neil Diamond. At No. 2 is Beethoven (!), with other Top 10 
sexual healers including Luther Vandross, Randy Travis (!), Kenny G., Glenn 
Miller (!!), Mozart and Led Zeppelin (!!!). Smokey and Madonna and the Chairman 
of the Board were nowhere to be found, all eclipsed by country picker Conway 
Twitty (!!!!), who finished 15th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
