<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROGER &amp; REALITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Socially conscious" film maker Michael Moore claims to have had the future and 
interests of Flint, Mich., residents in mind when he made "Roger &amp; Me." 
However, Moore is nothing greater than a free-wheeling, opportunistic scavenger 
who, through clever editing and misleading distortion of facts, holds the 
residents and civic leaders of Flint up for derision and humiliation. 
</P>
<P>
Rather than ameliorating the problem or drawing sympathy for his beloved 
hometown, Moore's foul sense of humor and highly accessible media profile only 
serve to promote and further his own interest in establishing a career as 
another Hollywood icon. 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH BANK 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
