<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
DESIGN ; 
</P>
<P>
CHAMBER MATES FROM DOWN UNDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA THORNBURG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHERIDAN, the classy Australian showplace of the boudoir, has crossed the seas 
to anchor two outlets on our shores: a cozy shop in Costa Mesa's South Coast 
Plaza and a larger representative in the Century City Shopping Center. The 
merchandise, which includes every conceivable bedroom accessory -- sheets, 
duvet covers, comforters, beds, upholstery fabric, wallpaper, window 
treatments, lamps and much more -- runs the gamut from frilly to sleekly 
contemporary. 
</P>
<P>
But it's the sheets that are the unqualified Sheridan standouts: vibrant 
solid-colored linens that coordinate with exotic tropicals, men's-club paisleys 
and a couple of playful designs from Australian artist / designer Ken Done. For 
those who can't find what they want among the nine bedroom vignettes displayed, 
sales consultants are available to advise. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheridan, Century City Shopping Center, 10250 Santa Monica Blvd., Century 
City, (213) 286-1638, and South Coast Plaza, 333 Bristol, Costa Mesa, (714) 
540-9978. 
</P>
<P>
BARBARA THORNBURG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, accessorized bedroom 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
