<HEADLINE>
<P>
STRIPPER-POLITICIAN IN TAIWAN SENTENCED FOR PORNO MOVIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAIPEI, Taiwan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hsu Shao-tan, Taiwan's stripper-turned-politician, was sentenced Friday to 
three months in prison for making a pornographic movie, court officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Under Taiwan law, sentences of less than six months can be settled by paying a 
fine -- amounting in Hsu's case to only $310 -- instead of serving the time. 
Hsu did not appear in court for the sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
She admitted appearing in the movie but said the nude scenes were not of her 
body. 
</P>
<P>
Hsu narrowly lost a race for a seat in Parliament in December elections. She is 
still awaiting judgment in another case brought after she took off her clothes 
in front of the legislature. 
</P>
</TEXT>
