<P>
EX-SCHOOL CHIEF NAMED TO HOSPITAL DISTRICT BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James Riewer, a Redondo Beach resident and former superintendent of the South 
Bay Union High School District, was appointed Friday to the board of the South 
Bay Hospital District. 
</P>
<P>
He was named to fill former board member Mary Davis' unexpired term, which runs 
until November, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, a board member since 1983, resigned in January. The district grants 
money for public health programs in Redondo Beach, Hermosa Beach and Manhattan 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
A hospital board member during the 1970s, Riewer was a compromise choice after 
the board failed to break a deadlock between candidates Dick Fruin, a former 
board member who was defeated for reelection in 1984 and failed in a 1986 
attempt to return to the board, and Jeremy Evans, a former legal counsel to the 
hospital district. 
</P>
<P>
Riewer, who was appointed on a 4-0 vote, said the action "came as a complete 
surprise. . . . It kind of tickles my funny bone." Currently a member of the 
Los Angeles County Commission on Human Relations, he headed the high school 
district from 1970 until retiring in 1979. 
</P>
