<P>
DIGEST/ LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RICOCHETING BULLET STRIKES MAN IN CHIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Clarita man who locked himself in his bathroom after an argument 
Saturday was hit by a ricocheting bullet after his girlfriend fired at the 
door's lock, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Herman Espetia, 23, was shot in the chin about 2:13 a.m. and taken to Henry 
Mayo Newhall Community Hospital, where he was in stable condition Saturday 
afternoon, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The bullet went through the door, ricocheted off the sink and hit Espetia. 
</P>
<P>
His girlfriend, Gregoria Granados, 23, was arrested on suspicion of discharging 
a firearm in a grossly negligent manner. 
</P>
<P>
"She told him if he refused to come out, she was going to shoot the lock and 
she did," said Deputy John Bayliss. 
</P>
<P>
Granados was free on $5,000 bail Saturday night. The shooting occurred in 
Espetia and Granados' home in the 18800 block of Mandan Avenue, authorities 
said. 
</P>
