<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEL WEBB PLANS ADULT PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phoenix-based Del Webb Corp., one of the nation's biggest developers of 
active-adult communities, has purchased 1,570 acres in Riverside County and 
plans to build about 6,000 homes for people aged 55 or over. 
</P>
<P>
The site is near the intersection of Interstate 10 and Washington Street, in 
the unincorporated area of the county. 
</P>
<P>
The new community will include single-family homes and townhouses, as well as 
an 18-hole golf course, arts-and-crafts studios and meeting rooms. It will also 
include commercial buildings and several places of worship. 
</P>
<P>
The company plans to begin construction and sales in 1991. Completion of the 
project is expected to take about 10 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
