<P>
GAY APPLICANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I really want to believe that the government of the United States is great and 
fair. But I am constantly bombarded by things such as Irvine's Measure N and 
the Feb. 6 article concerning the upholding of the Defense Department's policy 
of "subjecting all homosexual applicants for 'secret' and 'top secret' 
clearance to more intense investigations than the other applicants." 
</P>
<P>
How can we label some forms of bigotry morally wrong while supporting and 
encouraging others? Why is being prejudiced against homosexuals accepted, while 
prejudices against other groups are condemned? 
</P>
<P>
All levels of government are contributing to the encouragement of this blatant 
form of bigotry. If we accept discrimination against this one group, what will 
stop us from discriminating against other groups? I don't understand how we 
allow this outright discrimination in a country that prides itself on being 
open to all people. 
</P>
<P>
RENEE LION 
</P>
