<P>
4 CHILDREN STRANGLED IN ENGLISH VILLAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four children were found dead in their beds Saturday in the town of Basildon 
and police said they had apparently been strangled. 
</P>
<P>
Kam Tong Ngai, the father of the three boys and one girl aged 4 months to 5 
years, discovered the bodies when he came home from his job at a Chinese 
restaurant, said police in Basildon, about 25 miles east of London. 
</P>
<P>
The mother of the children, Oitai Ngai, a 32-year-old Hong Kong native, was 
being questioned, police said, but no charges had been filed against her. 
</P>
</TEXT>
