in a Big Eight Conference game at Lawrence, Kan. 
</P>
<P>
Kansas (25-2, 8-2) was coming off a defeat at home to No. 2 Missouri earlier in 
the week. 
</P>
<P>
The Jayhawks trailed, 22-17, after 10 minutes following a 9-0 spurt by Nebraska 
(9-14, 2-8), but a 14-4 run gave Kansas a 44-36 lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Pritchard scored eight points as the Jayhawks outscored the Cornhuskers, 20-5, 
to start the second half. 
</P>
